<TITLE> Bangladesh observes World Red Crescent Day </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 8 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh on Friday observed the 150th World Red Cross and Red Crescent Day with the slogan: Our world is a mess; it's time to make your move. The day is celebrated each year in honour of Henry Dunant, founder of the International Red Cross Movement 150 years ago. Bangladesh Red Crescent Society took out a colourful procession starting from Holy Family Red Crescent Medical College Hospital in capital's Maghbazar to mark the day. The procession led by disaster management minister Abdur Razzaq and participated by Bangladesh Red Crescent Society activists ended at the National Press Club. The minister said the activists of the Red Cross and Red Crescent have a psyche to serve people for a cause. He urged the affluent section of society to help put the Bangladesh Red Crescent Society in a better financial footing. bd
